<image 1> What is the specific term for the juvenile stage of the white pine weevil found on a spruce branch?

A. Pupa
B. Don't know and don't want to guess
C. Worm
D. Maggot
E. Grub

The specific term for the juvenile stage of the white pine weevil found on a spruce branch is:

E. Grub

Grubs are the larval stage of many beetles, including the white pine weevil. They are typically C-shaped and have a soft body. The other options do not accurately describe the larval stage of this insect.
